'''Circarpous IV''', often called simply '''Circarpous''', was a [[Planet/Legends|planet]] in the [[Expansion Region/Legends|Expansion Region]], one of the financial [[Capital/Legends|capitals]] of the region.<ref name="TEA" />

==History==
{{Quote|We've heard rumors from Circarpous IV, about an important meeting that the underground leaders there were preparing for? A young woman, you say?|[[Governor/Legends|Governor]] [[Bin Essada/Legends|Bin Essada]], to [[Captain-Supervisor]] [[Grammel]]|<ref name="Splinter of the Mind's Eye">''[[Splinter of the Mind's Eye]]''</ref>}}
During the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], it was a major backer of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credit]]. Attempting to undermine the Republic economy, the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatists]] [[Battle of Circarpous IV|attacked]] the world many times, just as the Republic tried to undermine the Separatist economy by attacks on [[Mygeeto/Legends|Mygeeto]].<ref name="Tinker, Tailor, Soldier, Praji">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/source/praji/20090205.html|text=Tinker, Tailor, Soldier, Praji|int=Tinker, Tailor, Soldier, Praji}}</ref>

During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] many of its business leaders, fed up with [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] taxation, agreed to fund the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]].

The Rebels sent three [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wings]] from [[Red Squadron (Rebel Alliance)/Legends|Red Squadron]] to feint an [[Skirmish near Circarpous IV|attack]] on the [[Circarpous system/Legends|Circarpous system]] in order to gauge Imperial defenses. [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter/Legends|TIE Fighters]] fell for the bait and intercepted the Rebels near Circarpous IV. Despite being outnumbered, the Rebel ships destroyed the Imperials before leaving. The Rebels' success helped create sympathy for the Rebellion in the Circarpous system. The mission was later recreated as a simulation to help new Rebel pilots learn to overcome the odds.<ref name="Xwing" />

